title: WWE Jakked/Metal
resume: WWE Jakked and WWE Metal are professional wrestling television programs produced by World Wrestling Entertainment. Both shows aired syndicated weekly from 1999 until 2002 and replaced WWF Shotgun Saturday Night. Originally produced under the World Wrestling Federation banner, they were replaced by the similarly formatted WWE Bottom Line and WWE After Burn in syndication.
